The files in the debian directory will be copied to (and overwrite if
necessary) the packaging files of the reform-tools package in Debian.  Thus, if
you want to make changes to the debian/control file in Debian, copy the
original into the ./debian directory and then make your edits. This avoids
having to maintain a patch against the Debian packaging. The downside is, that
it is now necessary to regularly copy the desired changes from the Debian
packaging in Debian as those will otherwise get reverted.
